Hi all, so I also found this issues. It was reported [here](https://bugs.python.org/issue33211) to python and was fixed by https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/9731. However, this change didn't make it to python 3.7.

In the python bug report they reference https://github.com/PyCQA/pyflakes/pull/273 which includes a handy workaround. Should that maybe be used in pylint?

@Pierre-Sassoulas what do you think. I'm willing to open a PR. Maybe astroid is the better place?
